gw.api.databuilder

Class BenefitsBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.databuilder.DataBuilder<T,B>
      • gw.api.databuilder.CCDataBuilder<Benefits,BenefitsBuilder>
        • gw.api.databuilder.BenefitsBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ValueGenerator<Benefits>

    public class BenefitsBuilder
extends CCDataBuilder<Benefits,BenefitsBuilder>
    Builder for Benefits objects which give detailed information about benefits. Benefits objects are peculiar in that they have no back pointer to claim, exposure or any other major data model type. Instead, different types of exposure have foreign keys to Benefits objects (for example PIP exposures have DeathBenefits, LifePensionBenefits, PPDBenefits, PTDBenefits, TPDBenefits, TTDBenefits and VocBenefits). So the usual usage of this builder will be to create benefit objects to add to an exposure e.g: exposureBuilder.withXXXBenefits(new BenefitsBuilder()....). Many of these benefits sub objects don't have any required fields so there is no UI ready builder for benefits.
